description.narrative: UNICEF’s social media platforms reached a new high of 551,760 followers. COVID-19 opened opportunities for innovative initiatives, such as a virtual field visit to the plastic bricks project. Another innovation was the appointment of a regional photographer, based in Abidjan and covering Burkina Faso, Cameroon, Chad, Niger, and Côte d’Ivoire. UNICEF Inspire (a TEDx style event) provided an opportunity for colleagues, partners, and beneficiaries to share personal experiences on their relationship with UNICEF Côte D’Ivoire, and was watched over 28,000 times. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:28/01/2022
